PyDSnap 0.3

               .-.
              ((`-'       <-^-^-^-^-^-^-^-^-^-^-^-^-^-^-^-^->
               \\         <                                 >
                \\        |          PyDSnap 2010           |
         .="""=._))       <                                 >
        ;  '=. "'"        <-v-v-v-v-v-v-v-v-v-v-v-v-v-v-v-v->
         '=="

Captures stock price snapshot of the Dhaka & Chittagong Stock Exchanges and 
generates CSV output in the standard OHLC format

(Compatible with AmiBroker, Meta Stock, Trade Station, Ninja Trader & other 
technical analysis tools)

Portions Coyright 2010 M Nasimul Haque <nasim.haque--AT--gmail.com>
Portions Coyright 2010 Dr. Masroor Ehsan Choudhury <masroore--AT--gmail.com>

Usage:
	./dsnap.py [options]
	
Options:
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -e, --header          append a header line to the CSV file (default: off)
  -d, --dse             capture DSE snapshot (default: on)
  -c, --cse             capture CSE snapshot (default: off)
  -f FILE, --file=FILE  save CSV data to FILE
  -v, --verbose         log status information on the screen (default: on)
  -q, --quiet
  -p, --print           print captured data on screen (default: off)
  -n, --dont-prune      do not filter out non-trading companies (default: off)
  -r OPT_REPEAT_INTERVAL, --repeat=OPT_REPEAT_INTERVAL
                        set the repeat interval (default: 1 minute)